Title: Attitudes on Life and Death
InvestigatorErin Buchanan, Ph.D.
Department of Psychology
128 Glen IsleMissouri State University417-836-5592
 Description:
This study will investigate the participant's attitudes on questions about life and death. If you feel troubled answering the questions, please feel free to opt out of the survey.  Your information will be kept confidential.  Risks and Benefits:
Participants may feel uncomfortable while taking this questionnaire.  You may leave the experiment at any time and are not required to fill out all the questions. At the end of the survey you will be redirected to a prompt to enter your Amazon MTurk account number to be compensated.Confidentiality:
We will not put your name on any of your tests.  Only Dr. Buchanan and her assistant will have access to the data collected for this study.  All data associated with this study will remain confidential. Right to Withdraw:
You do not have to take part in this study.  If you start the study and decide that you do not want to finish, all you have to do is close your survey window.  IRB Approval:
This study has been reviewed by Missouri State Universityâ€™s Institutional Review Board (IRB).  The IRB has determined that this study fulfills the human research subject protections obligations required by state and federal law and University policies.  If you have any questions, concerns, or reports regarding your rights as a participant of research, please contact the Office Research Compliance at 836-4132.Statement of Consent:
